latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So this is a little snippet to my full YouTube video on how to curl your hair! The video will be up today at 12.30pm so definitely check it out! Also, please do excuse me, I kept saying “a tong” when I actually used a wand. You can use a 32mm tong for this look as well! A tong just has a clamp but I don’t use the clamp when I curl the hair, for this particular hairstyle. Stay tuned for part 2 on how to create different styles with this hair 😘💗
-
Products used: - @avedauk Damage Remedy “Daily Hair Repair” to prep on wet hair before styling
- @bombayhair 5-in-1 32mm curling wand
- @schwarzkopf Silhouette Flexible Hold Spray

latestPosts.caption:
A follower of mine asked about my current makeup routine, so a new YouTube video drops this Sunday at 6PM UK time!💄✨

It’s a chatty GRWM where I share my must have makeup products, talk about my friend visiting Japan 🇯🇵, and reveal my love for anime (something most people don’t know about me 👀)

Did you watch anime growing up? 👀

As a petite and curvy girl, finding clothes that fit right has always been a struggle. Trousers that are too long, blazers that don’t sit properly, trench coats that overwhelm my frame-I’ve been there! 😩

That’s why getting these pieces tailor-made in Hoi An was a total game-changer! ✨ For the first time, I didn’t have to compromise on fit-everything was made exactly for my body. The trench coat, blazer, and trousers actually sit where they’re supposed to, and honestly, it makes all the difference.

Wearing clothes that actually fit properly doesn’t just look better, it makes me feel better-more put-together, more confident, and way less frustrated when getting dressed😍

So to all my fellow petite & curvy girls-if you get the chance, I highly recommend getting things tailored. It’s so worth it!

Would you ever get custom-made pieces? Let me know in the comments!☺️✨

Signed up for the Coconut Forest Bamboo Boat Tour expecting a calm ride… instead, I got a full-on party on water 🎤💃🏽😂 

One minute we’re floating peacefully, the next it’s karaoke, spinning boats, and dance-offs-sensory overload, but I was so here for it!! 🤣

I would highly recommend this is if you visit Hoi An!
